Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need
to peel). Trim the @aubergine{1} then halve lengthways. Chop each half into
four long strips, then chop widthways into roughly 2cm pieces. Peel and grate
the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pop the potato and aubergine onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with
@oil{for roasting}, season with @salt{for roasting} and @pepper{for roasting}
then sprinkle over the garlic. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single
layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Once your oven is hot, roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden,
~{30-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, pat the @cod fillets{2} with #kitchen paper{} to remove any excess
moisture and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Line another baking tray with
#baking paper{} and lay on the cod fillets. Spread the @fresh pesto{50%g}
evenly over the top of the fillets. Set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish.

== Tomato Parsley Salsa ==

Quarter the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}. Roughly chop the
@flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all). Zest the
@lemon{1/2} then chop into wedges. Pop the tomatoes, parsley, lemon zest and
@olive oil{for the dressing} into a #medium bowl{}. Add a squeeze of lemon juice.
Mix together and season to taste with @salt{for salsa}, @pepper{for salsa} and
more lemon juice if needed. Set aside.

== Cooking the Cod ==

When 15 mins of veg roasting time remain, pop the cod on the middle shelf of
your oven and roast until cooked, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

== To Serve ==

When everything is ready, divide the roast potatoes and aubergine between your
plates. Top with the pesto cod and salsa. Serve with any lemon wedges
alongside for squeezing over. Enjoy!